console.log(employee.salary); // prints $50,000
```
In this example, the `data` variable is treated as if it were of type `User`, `Organization`, and `Employee`, even though it does not have a strict type definition. This allows the code to be more flexible and adaptable to different types of data, and makes it easier to work with libraries and frameworks that do not provide strict type definitions.

